President Muhammadu Buhari last night hosted officials of Presidential Campaign Council (PCC) at the presidential villa, Abuja. In attendance, at the dinner which started around 8:10pm were the Director General of the PCC, Rotimi Amaechi, a former Senate President, Ken Nnmani, Senator Ali Ndume, Senator Abdullahi Adamu, a former chairman of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC), Nuhu Ribadu and Senator Bashir Lado. Others were the Secretary to the Government of the Federation, Boss Mustapha, Chief of Staff, Abba Kyari and Minister of Education, Adamu Adamu. The national leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Asiwaju Bola Tinubu who is expected to deliver a remark, according to the programme of event was absent, as at the time journalists were excused from the venue. Also, the national chairman of the APC, Adams Oshiomhole whose name was on the programme of the event was absent. The president who won his reelection set up the council in January with him as chairman and Tinubu as the co-chairman. JUST IN: Buhari hosts officials of presidential campaign council Buhari to inaugurate APC Presidential Campaign Council Monday Buhari inaugurates campaign council tomorrow